<h1 id="use-cases">Use Cases</h1>
<h2 id="tax-loss-harvesting">Tax Loss Harvesting</h2>
<p>Can I harvest my current losses in TECL, without losing exposure and triggering wash sales? Yes, you can! </p>
<p>1 <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/TECL.html">TECL</a></span> = 1 <span
            class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/UPRO.html">UPRO</a></span> + 1 <span
            class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                href="/letf-summary/TQQQ.html">TQQQ</a></span> (<a href="/letf-summary/overlaps/TECL_UPRO_TQQQ.html">72.53%
        combined overlap</a>)! </p>
<h4 id="solve-how-many-shares-you-need-to-swap-with">Solve how many shares you need to swap with</h4>
<p>(Number of shares of TECL owned) * (Price of TECL share) = X * (Price of UPRO share) + X * (Price of TQQQ
    share).</p>
<p>Solve for X!</p>
<p>On July 27th, 2020,</p>
<ul>
    <li><span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/TECL.html">TECL</a></span> is at $36.40</li>
    <li><span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/UPRO.html">UPRO</a></span> is at $41.39</li>
    <li><span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/TQQQ.html">TQQQ</a></span> is at $30.74</li>
    <li>I own 1385 shares, whose average purchase price is $50.00</li>
</ul>
<p>Substituting we get </p>
<p>36.40 * 1385 / (41.39 + 30.74) ~= 699 = X!</p>
<h5 id="harvested-loss">Harvested Loss</h5>
<p>While keeping approximately 73% of the same exposure, you&#39;ve captured approximately 18,836$ worth of tax losses
    which are not eligible for Wash Sale (assuming no more transactions on TECL)</p>
