<h2 id="increase-leverage-">Increase Leverage!</h2>
<p>I own 100 shares of <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/SPY.html">SPY</a></span>, and I
    believe that <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/SPY.html">SPY</a></span> is going to
    increase. Let me dial up the leverage to 2x by adopting
    <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/QLD.html">QLD</a></span> and <span
            class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/SSO.html">SSO</a></span>.</p>
<p>On July 26th, 2022: </p>
<ul>
    <li><span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/SPY.html">SPY</a></span> is at $390.90</li>
    <li><span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/QLD.html">QLD</a></span> is at $45.39</li>
    <li><span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/SSO.html">SSO</a></span> is at $48.</li>
</ul>
<p>100 * 390 = X * 45.39 + X * 48</p>
<p>X ~= 417. So you buy 417 shares of <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/QLD.html">QLD</a></span>
